contributions.title: Cult Of Snap (Remix)
contributions.notes:
The frontcover of this release does have the typical "Snap!-Logo-Box" in the left upper corner but the also typical "Snap!-Hand" is missing. This is simulair to "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/5907710]Version 2[/url]" of the original CD-Maxi.

Also in the left under corner there is not the typical "Snap!-hand" but 4 times the word 'Snap!'. Also just like "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/5907710]Version 2[/url]" of the original CD-Maxi.
And where by most original versions of the CD-Maxi "Original Version" appears is a question-mark instead, just like the original "[url=https://www.discogs.com/release/85238]Version 1[/url]". 

This second variant has a complete different back artwork with pictures from the original music video, just like the back artwork of "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/11607043]Version 4 of the Original CD-Maxi[/url]".

contributions.title: Cult Of Snap
contributions.notes:
Release variant 5 with slightly different sleeve, and little errors.

Actually this release is almost identical to "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/11606457]Version 3[/url]".
Only this was the first printing with another matrix-runout number (A4 instead of A6 in it) and contained some errors that were fixed by  "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/11606457]Version 3[/url]".

This release contains the typical "Snap!" logo in the left upper corner complete with the also typical "Snap!" hand.
Also on the left under corner there appears the text "Original Version" instead of the '?' (Question Mark) by version 1, and the "Snap! - Hand" appears also.

On the sideflip the text is written incorrect by writing trough another text. It's about the 'Logic Records' logo in pink.
A last note is that by this fifth variant on the back cover, track 4 has a half letter. It's about the 'P' in 'Cult Of Snap'.

Also exist "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/85238]Version 1[/url]" , "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/5907710]Version 2[/url]" , "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/11606457]Version 3[/url]" and "[url=https://www.discogs.com/Snap-Cult-Of-Snap/release/11607043]Version 4[/url]".

contributions.title: Chartbusters April 1993 (Dance Edition)
contributions.notes:
Since the beginning of the pressing of the monthly illegal 'Chartbusters CD's' back in July/August 1992, the series started to have a month CD as well only with extended remix versions.

This should be especially for the DJ's around in the clubs and also were only available by person to person without knowing anything about the whole CD, such as release dates.

As a matter of fact these "extra CD's" in 1 month did double the costs for the random customer up to HFL 50,- instead of the normal HFL 25,- and this success wasn't about to last long.

There came only 3 editions of this so called "Chartbusters Dance Edition" , February 1993, March 1993 and as last April 1993.
